      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(slack): add ignoreOtherMentions channel config",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add `ignoreOtherMentions` option for Slack channel config, mirroring the existing Discord guild/channel feature\n- When enabled, messages that mention another user (`<@U...>`) but do not explicitly mention the bot are dropped — even inside bot-participated threads\n- This prevents the bot from replying when a user is talking to a coworker in a thread where the bot previously responded\n\n## Slack vs Discord difference\n\nDiscord's `ignoreOtherMentions` checks `!wasMentioned && !implicitMention`. The Slack version intentionally omits the `!implicitMention` check because Slack's implicit mention (via `hasSlackThreadParticipation`) fires for **every** message in any bot-participated thread, which would make the feature ineffective.\n\n## Config example\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    slack: {\n      channels: {\n        \"*\": { ignoreOtherMentions: true },\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n## Changed files\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/config/types.slack.ts` | Add `ignoreOtherMentions` to `SlackChannelConfig` |\n| `src/config/zod-schema.providers-core.ts` | Add zod validation for the new field |\n| `extensions/slack/src/monitor/channel-config.ts` | Wire through type + resolver |\n| `extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.ts` | Drop logic before mention gating |\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `pnpm build` passes\n- [x] `pnpm test -- extensions/slack/src/monitor` — 236 tests pass\n- [x] Manual test on live Slack workspace: bot no longer replies when tagging a coworker in a bot thread\n- [x] Bot still replies when explicitly @mentioned in the same thread\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
